In computing, an execution context is the environment in which code is executed. It contains the information needed for \the
 program to run correctly, such as:

Variables and their values
Function parameters
The current scope
The call stack
this binding (in languages like JavaScript)
Instruction pointer/program counter (at a lower level)
                                                                                                                                            

